Polymorphism & Composition Homework Quiz

=== Polymorphism ===

1 - What does the word polymorphism mean?

    The concept that two classes in a program can be treated as if they were the
    same.

2 - What does it mean when we apply polymorphism to OO design? Give a simple
    Java example.

    ???

3 - What can we use to implement polymorphism in Java?

    Interfaces and Abstract classes from which other classes inherit attributes.

4 - How many 'forms' can an object take when using polymorphism?

    There is no hard limit to the number of forms an object can take. There is
    soft limit of 65535, but the chances of one reaching that amount are remote.

5 - give an example of when you could use polymorphism.

    ???

=== Composition ===

6 - What do we mean by 'composition' in reference to object-oriented
    programming?

    The act of combining different classes in a single function?

7 - When would you use composition? Provide a simple example in Java

    When a class needs to incorporate several attributes in order to utilise a
    function

